mediator.common.modifiers module#

class mediator.common.modifiers.ModifierFactory[source]#

Bases: object

Modifier factory.

Factory that produces action callable, that wraps given callable into it with extra behaviour.

create(call, **kwargs)[source]#

Produces action callable that wraps given one with extra behaviour.

Example: >>> class SomeModifierFactory: >>> def create(self, call: ActionCallType, **kwargs) -> ActionCallType: >>> async def wrapper(action: ActionSubject) -> ActionResult: >>> # … extra logic for arguments inspection or modification >>> result = await call(action) >>> # … extra logic for result inspection or modification >>> return result >>> >>> return wrapper

Parameters

  • call (Callable[[ActionSubject], Awaitable[ActionResult]]) – callable to be wrapped

  • kwargs – extra context information; currently contains:

Return type

Callable[[ActionSubject], Awaitable[ActionResult]]

target - final callable in stack (if stack of modifiers is built) :return: wrapped action callable that calls given one and acts with arguments or result

class mediator.common.modifiers.ModifierStack[source]#

Bases: object

Utility for build modifier stacks that wraps action callable.

classmethod build(factories, call)[source]#

Builds modifier stack action callable wrapper from factory sequence.

Factory sequence is projected directly onto call trace. For example: if factories [Af, Bf, Cf] produce [A, B, C] modifiers, call stack will be organized as: A -> B -> C -> call :param factories: sequence of modifier factory to wrap given callable recursively :param call: action callable to be recursively wrapped by modifiers :return: wrapped action callable that contains behaviour of all modifiers in given order

Parameters

  • factories (Sequence[ModifierFactory]) –

  • call (Callable[[ActionSubject], Awaitable[ActionResult]]) –

Return type

Callable[[ActionSubject], Awaitable[ActionResult]]
